com.vdom.core

Class CardSet

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.vdom.core.CardSet

  • public class CardSet
extends java.lang.Object
    This class contains a set of cards (for a given GameType) that can be used. If the GameType value is one of the random sets, a random CardSet is generated using the available cards specified. Note that the sets defined in the actual Dominion rule books are created when the application loads. These are created in a static block at the end of the class.

      • getRandomCardSet

        private static CardSet getRandomCardSet(java.util.List<Card> possibleCards)
        This returns a random CardSet using a subset of the cards entered as a parameter. Note that a bane card is set aside every time to avoid having to swap out a card after the entire set is selected. If a bane card is not required, that value is simply cleared away.
        Parameters:
        possibleCards - The set of cards that can be included in the random CardSet
        Returns:
        A random CardSet selected from the list of entered cards.
